Aetna Inc. (; stylized as Ã¦tna) is an American managed health care company, which sells traditional and consumer directed health care insurance plans and related services, such as medical, pharmaceutical, dental, behavioral health, long-term care, and disability plans. Aetna is a member of the Fortune 500.
In June 2017, the company announced plans to move its headquarters to New York City in late 2018. On December 3, 2017, it was announced that CVS would purchase Aetna for an estimated $69 billion, a deal which the New York Times reported would "reshape the American health care industry."
